{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "b7e1f4c2-9a3d-4e7b-bb10-island-combo-001",
    "name": "Island Combo API (Bearer JWT)",
    "description": "Standard Bearer-token API for the final-ecom app.\n\nHOW TO USE\n1. Set the `baseUrl` collection variable (default http://localhost:3000).\n2. Run **Auth > Login** with a real email/password. The test script auto-saves `accessToken` + `refreshToken` into collection variables.\n3. Every request under **User**, **Admin**, and **Cash Vouchers** inherits `Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}` automatically — just hit Send.\n4. When the token expires (~1h), run **Auth > Refresh Token** to get a fresh one (also auto-saved).\n\nNOTES\n- Auth is the Supabase access token (ES256). It already carries sub/email/user_role; nothing extra to do.\n- **Admin** and **Cash Vouchers** endpoints require an admin/staff token (a customer token gets 403).\n- **Public** endpoints send no token.\n- Email confirmation is ON, so Sign Up returns a token only after the email is confirmed; use Login for testing.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      { "key": "token", "value": "{{accessToken}}", "type": "string" }
    ]
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:3000", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "accessToken", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "refreshToken", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login (saves tokens)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('login ok', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.eql(200));",
                  "if (res && res.data && res.data.accessToken) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', res.data.accessToken);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('refreshToken', res.data.refreshToken);",
                  "  console.log('Saved accessToken + refreshToken. role =', res.data.role);",
                  "} else {",
                  "  console.warn('No tokens in response:', JSON.stringify(res));",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [ { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" } ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"you@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"your-password\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login",
              "host": [ "{{baseUrl}}" ],
              "path": [ "api", "auth", "login" ]
            },
            "description": "Returns { role, redirectTo, accessToken, refreshToken, expiresAt, tokenType }. The test script saves accessToken + refreshToken for every other request."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Sign Up",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [ { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" } ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"newuser@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"your-password\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/signup",
              "host": [ "{{baseUrl}}" ],
              "path": [ "api", "auth", "signup" ]
            },
            "description": "Email confirmation is ON, so the token bundle is returned only once the email is confirmed. Use Login to obtain a token for testing."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Refresh Token (saves tokens)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('refresh ok', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.eql(200));",
                  "if (res && res.data && res.data.accessToken) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', res.data.accessToken);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('refreshToken', res.data.refreshToken);",
                  "  console.log('Refreshed accessToken + refreshToken.');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [ { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" } ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"refreshToken\": \"{{refreshToken}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/refresh",
              "host": [ "{{baseUrl}}" ],
              "path": [ "api", "auth", "refresh" ]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
